\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. H. speciosa} (R. Cunn. ex A. Cunn.) Andersen,{\i  Trans. Proc. N.Z. Inst.}{\b  56}: 693 (1926). Up to 150 cm, of compact habit. Young twigs glabrous. Leaves 5-10 × 2·5-5 cm, obovate-oblong coriaceous to fleshy, glabrous. Racemes 7-10 cm, stout, very dense. Calyx 2 mm. Corolla violet to reddish-purple; lobes c. 4 mm, broadly ovate, obtuse, erecto-patent. Capsule 5-6 × 3-4 mm.{\i  Cultivated for ornament, and for hedges near the sea; locally naturalized on sea-cliffs in Ireland.} [?Br Hb.] ({\i New Zealand.})
