\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 23.                 Paederota}                   L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By D.A. Webb.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs; leaves opposite, undivided. Flowers in terminal, bracteate, spike-like racemes. Calyx somewhat unequally 5-lobed. Corolla with cylindrical tube and 2-lipped limb, usually somewhat shorter than the tube; upper lip entire (rarely 2-lobed), erect; lower lip 3-lobed, more or less patent. Stamens 2, exserted from corolla-tube, but sometimes shorter than limb. Stigma capitate. Capsule loculicidal, not laterally compressed; seeds numerous.
\par

